			<h3 class="first"><a href="#p972">Collision Component / Trigger Component</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=972&amp;sid=a8463ede43783c737354840a82a9a968#p972"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Mensagem" title="Mensagem" /></a>por <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53&amp;sid=a8463ede43783c737354840a82a9a968" style="color: #000066;" class="username-coloured">bruno.duartec</a></strong> &raquo; 20 Jun 2011, 12:53 </p>

			

			<div class="content">Yesterday i was taking a look at the trigger component, but there is still a lot of issues to solve. <br /><br />Thinking about how to solve collisions and talking to thelinuxlich i will try to make a collisioncomponent, wich keeps this informations:<br /> ObjectA, ObjectB, collisiontime, force<br /><br />I am going to make an extension of the IObject with a Tag field, in wich we can trade simple informations between objects, i will store the entityid in it, to can retrieve in the moment of the collision an create a collision component<br /><br />I am aware of the trigger hierarqui, but i don´t know how to create a trigger component. Today i will make a little essays</div>

			<div id="sig972" class="signature">PloobsEngine<br />Creator and Developer<br />ploobsengine.codeplex.com<br />ploobs.com.br</div>

		</div>

		
