			<h3 ><a href="#p974">Re: Collision Component / Trigger Component</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=974&amp;sid=a8463ede43783c737354840a82a9a968#p974"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Mensagem" title="Mensagem" /></a>por <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54&amp;sid=a8463ede43783c737354840a82a9a968" style="color: #000066;" class="username-coloured">tpastor</a></strong> &raquo; 20 Jun 2011, 13:10 </p>

			

			<div class="content">Sincerely, i still thinking that the entity component should not deal with this stuffs.<br />The engine must take care about this =P<br /><br />The best aproach, in my opinion, would be:<br />The artemis/ploobs interface should be done using messages (ploobs messages).<br />The engine and Artemis dont talk directely. (artemis only have a  component that has an instance of an IObject. Only this =P)<br /><br />The components (the artemis ones) could be made to recieve Messages, and those be processed by the systems. (just a possible idea)<br /><br />in my point of view, Trying to mix artemis and ploobs wont work &gt;.&lt; (if works, things will be unstable, unreliable, pog ....). Reasons:<br />1-&gt; you have two VERY diferent paradigms that deal with problems in VERY diferent ways<br />2-&gt;You will have to do everything twice (we already have a wrapper to bepu trigger in ploobs, you will make another artemis wrapper for the ploobs wrapper for the bepu trigger ..... )<br /><br />Exchanging Messages is the solution =P<br />Want to create a trigger in the &quot;artemis side&quot;, send a message to some factory (factory will be in the ploobs &quot;domain&quot;)<br />The trigger founds something in the &quot;ploobs domain&quot;, he send a message to you in the &quot;artemis domain&quot; ...<br /><br />Extend this concept to other areas.<br /><br />This is important, if wrong choices were made were .... shit WILL HAPPEN, lets discuss =P</div>

			<div id="sig974" class="signature">PloobsEngine<br />Creator and Developer<br />ploobs.com.br/?page_id=1381</div>

		</div>

		
