			<h3 ><a href="#p977">Re: Collision Component / Trigger Component</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=977&amp;sid=a8463ede43783c737354840a82a9a968#p977"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Mensagem" title="Mensagem" /></a>por <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=97&amp;sid=a8463ede43783c737354840a82a9a968" style="color: #000066;" class="username-coloured">thelinuxlich</a></strong> &raquo; 20 Jun 2011, 14:21 </p>

			

			<div class="content">One way of abstracting event messages into an Entity System is by representing these messages as Components. Each System has Added(), Process() and Removed() which you can override with your own logic to intercept entities with Components onAdd/onRemove or during normal processing.</div>

			

		</div>

		
