			<h3 ><a href="#p986">Re: Collision Component / Trigger Component</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=986&amp;sid=a8463ede43783c737354840a82a9a968#p986"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Mensagem" title="Mensagem" /></a>por <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54&amp;sid=a8463ede43783c737354840a82a9a968" style="color: #000066;" class="username-coloured">tpastor</a></strong> &raquo; 20 Jun 2011, 18:15 </p>

			

			<div class="content">edited the previuos post =P<br />i told that cause the message system works acummulating messages and sending them at once. (and it has a number of messages that he can send each frame).<br />some messages can be senr lots of times to an object, if the message is a component, it would be strange.<br />messages are used to tell something about the engine (triggers for example notifies objects using messages)<br />if you put components as messages, you are coupling both systems too much.<br /><br />We should have the engine and the artemis as isolated systems (of course some things will be shared)<br />and the messages being the way informations are changed.<br />In the artemis side:<br />Components &quot;intercepts&quot; messages and the systems process them.<br />Components also can send messages to the engine  (i mean, the sustem send, using the component id as the send id, no violation of the data only principle =P)</div>

			<div id="sig986" class="signature">PloobsEngine<br />Creator and Developer<br />ploobs.com.br/?page_id=1381</div>

		</div>

		
